<MELItem itemNbr="73-21-03" id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.MEL.2-73-21-03.1.2-73-21-03_FAA">
<Title>EEC C1 Faults</Title>
<MELSubItem itemNbr="73-21-03-02">
<Title>GE</Title>
<DispatchCondition repairInterval="A" nbrInstalled="2" nbrRequired="0" maintIndicator="(M)">
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>May be dispatched with C1 faults provided repairs are made within 150 flight hours.</Para>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
<DispatchProcedure>
<MaintenanceProcedure>
<Para>Prior to each flight with EICAS Status Message ENG EEC C1 X (where “X” is the engine position “L” or “R”), check for the fault combinations in the Table.  Dispatch of an airplane is prohibited if the status message “ENG EEC C1 X”, and any of the following conditions exist:</Para>
<List listType="1.">
<ListItem>
<Para>None of the maintenance messages in the Central Maintenance Computing Function (CMCF) correlate with the “ENG EEC C1 X” status message; or</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>The following maintenance message fault codes combination exists in the CMCF for either channel A or B (where "X" is the engine position "1" or "2"): </Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
<table frame="all">
<tgroup cols="2" colsep="1">
<colspec colname="1" colwidth="33%" />
<colspec colname="2" colwidth="67%" />
<thead>
<row rowsep="1">
<entry colname="1">
<Para>
<Emphasis txtStyle="bold">Fault Combination Description</Emphasis>
</Para>
</entry>
<entry colname="2">
<Para>
<Emphasis txtStyle="bold">Corresponding Fault Codes Combination</Emphasis>
</Para>
<Para align="left" />
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row rowsep="1">
<entry colname="1" morerows="1">
<Para align="left">{TLA out of range fault} AND</Para>
<Para align="left">{FMV/FSV disagree fault OR FMV/FSV out of range fault (on the same channel as TLA out of range fault)}</Para>
<Para align="left" />
</entry>
<entry colname="2">
<Para align="left">{76-1953X (CH-A)}
AND
{73-3204X OR 73-3121X OR 73-1205X OR 73-1122X}</Para>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep="0">
<entry colname="2">
<Para align="left">{76-2953X (CH-B)}
AND
{73-3204X OR 73-3121X OR 73-2205X OR 73-2122X}</Para>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</MaintenanceProcedure>
</DispatchProcedure>
</DispatchCondition>
</MELSubItem>
</MELItem>
</DispatchItems>